        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:54PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Southeast Arcadia, or near Arcadia, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeast Arcadia, Arcadia, Lake Suzy, Nocatee, Babcock Webb Wma,
Babcock Ranch, Harbour Heights, Fort Ogden, Cleveland, and North
Port.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
